race.comment: NOIR VITESSE (2) returns and makes his stable debut for Darrell Burnett. Showed some positive signs last campaign and looks to have come back in good order, taking benefit from a nice trial here in readiness. Can make the perfect return. MY MATE ELVIS (9) showed early speed from a good draw last time but tired late at Canberra Acton. Has been freshened for this third-up assignment and must respect the stable decision to remove the blinkers. Can improve sharply. INSTIGATE (5) has been thereabouts in her first two starts without threatening. Fitter again and gets in well with the claim. Has upside, so worth some thought. BELNERA (4) showed plenty of promise when resuming but has struggled to go on with it. Can give her another chance in a thin race. Debutant SWIFT ARTIE (12) from the Craig Weeding camp looks best of the rest.
